# MARACE: Interaction Race Detection via Happens-Before–Aware Abstract Interpretation for Multi-Agent RL Safety Verification

**MARACE** (Multi-Agent Race Analysis and Certification Engine) is a
verification system that detects timing-dependent safety violations in
asynchronous multi-agent reinforcement-learning systems.  When independently
deployed policies share a physical environment but observe and act with
heterogeneous latencies, the relative ordering of their actions is
unconstrained—and certain interleavings can trigger safety violations
invisible to any single-agent analysis.  MARACE formalises these failures as
**interaction races** and provides sound detection, probability estimation,
and absence certification.

## Architecture

```
 ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
 │                           MARACEPipeline                                    │
 │                  (pipeline.py — stage orchestrator)                          │
 └──┬──────┬──────┬──────┬──────┬──────┬──────┬──────┬──────┬──────┬──────┬────┘
    │      │      │      │      │      │      │      │      │      │      │
 ┌──┴──┐┌──┴──┐┌──┴──┐┌──┴──┐┌──┴──┐┌──┴──┐┌──┴──┐┌──┴──┐┌──┴──┐┌──┴──┐┌──┴──┐
 │Load ││Conf ││Parse││Rec. ││Build││Decom││Abstr││Adver││Impor││Cata-││Repor│
 │Poli-││ Env ││Spec ││Trace││ HB  ││pose ││ act ││sari-││tance││ log ││ting │
