## Key Algorithms

### Zonotope abstract domain

A zonotope **Z = {c + G·ε | ε ∈ [-1,1]^p}** is defined by a centre vector
c ∈ ℝⁿ and generator matrix G ∈ ℝⁿˣᵖ.  Affine transforms are exact;
ReLU/Tanh activations are soundly over-approximated via DeepZ-style
λ-relaxation.  Generator count is bounded by Girard's PCA-based reduction.

### HB-aware transfer functions

After each abstract transfer step the zonotope is intersected with
halfspaces **aᵀx ≤ b** encoding happens-before ordering and timing
constraints derived from the causal graph.  This prunes the abstract
state to only HB-consistent joint states.

### MCTS adversarial schedule search

UCB1 with a safety-margin bias explores the schedule space.  Only
HB-consistent interleavings are expanded (via `HBConsistencyPruner`
and `SymmetryPruner`).  Abstract safety margins guide the search
toward low-margin (risky) regions.

### Compositional decomposition

Agents are partitioned into interaction groups via spectral or min-cut
methods.  Each group is verified independently under assume-guarantee
contracts on shared state variables.  The composition is sound:
any global interaction race projects onto at least one group.

### Importance sampling

Race probability is estimated via sequential importance sampling with
cross-entropy proposal adaptation.  Confidence intervals are computed
using Hoeffding / Bernstein bounds and Bayesian posterior estimation.

